# AvtTools version 2.7p4 Release Notes
# Copyright (c) 1998-2005, AVERTEC All Rights Reserved
# September 7th, 2005
#
###############################################################################

# 1 - New functionalities
  - The log file mechanism has been re-built and unified. It is now activated 
  with the variables avtLogFile and avtLogEnable. The avtCharacTraceLevel and 
  yagleTraceLevel variables become obsolete, as well as the MBK_TRACE_FILE, 
  MBKLOGFILE and MBK_SPI_DISPLAY_IGNORED environment variables.
  - The avtSpiInputVector variable allows configuration of input vectors 
  recognition.
  - The following Tcl functions have been added
    * stb_GetSignalHold
    * stb_GetSignalSetup
    * stb_DisplayConnectorToLatchError
    * stb_DisplaySlackReport
    * ttv_SetupReport
    * ttv_RemoveDuplicatedPath
    * inf_DefineSlopeRange
    * inf_DefineCapacitanceRange

# 2 - Major functionality Changes
  - The include parameter has been added to the avtSpiParseFirstLine variable 
  - The avtDoNotDevectNames variable becomes avtVectorize
  - The avtSpiNotMergeConnector variable becomes avtSpiMergeConnector
  - The inf_DefineIgnore Tcl function accepts the new argument SignalNames, 
  used to filter undesirable names when flattening a netlist.
  - Hiding the dt.linetype column in the ttv_DisplayPathDetailHideColumn Tcl 
  function activates the merge of RC and gate delays in reports.
  - The STR file now shows the transparency time of latches.

# 3 - Enhancements
  - The existence of the signals specified in the INF file is now checked during 
  the execution. The check is done as soon as possible, issuing the following 
  message: [Info][inf] Check level I/II/II.
  - Section Ignore in the INF file has a new sub section: SignalNames, used to 
  filter undesirable names when flattening a netlist.
  - The "Get Detailed Path" intermediate window has been suppressed in the Xtas 
  GUI.
  

