    - Linux   : RedHat 8.0 and RedHat Enterprise Linux 3.0
  
  
# IMPORTANT note:
A new license file is required to use the v2.7 release as the Flexnet tokens
structure has been modified in order to integrate new features and match
product offering.


  This document describes (1) New functionalities, (2) Major functionality 
Changes, (3) Enhancements, (4) Tools included within this version,
(5) Linux configuration.

# 1 - New functionalities
  - Enhanced slope modeling
  - Current induced behavior
  - Ideal clock
  - Netlist ignore elements
  - Advance MS deck generation

# 2 - Major functionality Changes
  - Tas binary has disappeared and is now fully included within HiTas
  - New TCL API structure
  - New documentation system
  - Some variables and options have changed:
    * Semantic of avt(Vdd|Vss)Name and avtGlobal(Vdd|Vss)Name changed to reflect use of
      Spice Vcards and .GLOBAL directive, these variables are no longer required if
      Supplies are specified in the Spice netlist
    * XtasDatabaseFilter no longer supported
    * tasbreakloops no longer supported
    * Option -bk no longer supported
    * "slew" becomes "slope" in STM file
    * infDefineSlope replaces infDefineSlew in INF Apis
    * "PINSLOPE" replaces "PINSLEW" in INF file
    * tasInputConnectorSlope replaces tasInputConnectorSlew configuration variable.

# 3 - Enhancements
  - Enhanced diode modeling
  - Improved spice card handling
  - Optimized delay calculator
  
